===Etymology===
Mitford Mathews suggested in 1951 that the term was derived from {{m|en||brot|scrap(s), small amount(s)}},<ref name="Cassidy">F. G. Cassidy, ''Etymology in Caribbean Creoles'', in ''Focus on the Caribbean'' (ISBN 9027248664), which quotes Mathew's ''Dictionary of Americanisms'' (1951)</ref> a northern England dialectal term ultimately derived from {{m|ang|brēotan}},<ref>''The English Dialect Dictionary'' (1898)</ref> but Joey Lee Dillard finds this idea "unconvincing".<ref>Joey Lee Dillard, ''Toward a Social History of American English''</ref> Possibly from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|βρωτός||lang=grc|tr=brōtós|edible}}.
